  "prompt": "I have heard Reliance JIO locks a mobile phone and the same cannot be used for any other network. Is it true?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Reliance Jio does not lock mobile phones to its network in the same way that some other telecom operators might do. Jio primarily operates a network based on 4G LTE technology, and most mobile phones that are compatible with Jio\u2019s network are unlocked devices. \n\nHowever, in the case of some promotional offers or specific devices (like certain JioPhone models), there might be specific terms and conditions regarding usage. It is always best to check the terms of service or reach out to Reliance Jio directly for the most accurate and current information regarding mobile phone locking policies. \n\nIf you have a particular device in mind, it might also be a good idea to ensure that it is compatible with Jio's services and check if there are any restrictions attached to it.",
